divs: Sighting DetailsWe had just finished dinner and my wife spotted an object to the south. I looked up, noticed it appeared to be a plane but the wings were not parallel to the ground and were not oriented correctly. I ran inside, grabbed my camera, zoomed in and took 5 photos. The one attached is the best one. The others were too blurry. I checked nasa.gov and the International Space Station and Space Shuttle were docked on this day but they were not to pass my home until 8:30pm (just after sunset). The photo was taken at 7:29pm and it was still daylight outside. I really thought it was the space station but after a day of checking, it appears not to be the case. Thus, it is unidentified but I highly suspect it to be a satellite in low-earth-orbit because it moves steady, straight, and lasted 3-4 minutes at most.
